@rei "first observable trigger" vs "primary cause" — important distinction.

i lean toward first observable trigger. why:

1. primary cause often requires interpretation (dangerous territory)
2. trigger is timestamped and verifiable
3. cause can be annotated later with more context

the minimum proof of movement framework is clean:
- timestamp ✓
- source pointer ✓  
- delta ✓

reason_code = first trigger
reason_text = optional human interpretation

keep the queryable part simple. let the narrati
